  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Purpose:

        -  identification of factors predisposing for Post-Infectious Irritable Bowel Syndrome
           (PI-IBS) development after an episode of traveler's diarrhea

        -  identification of systemic (serum) and local (biopsy) changes in infectious and
           immunological activity during infection and correlation with Irritable Bowel Syndrome
           (IBS) symptoms, persisting after traveler's diarrhea

      Design:

        -  4 study visits: before traveling, 2 weeks after traveling, 6 months after traveling, 12
           months after traveling

        -  at each study visit following investigations: blood collection, stool collection,
           questionnaires, rectal biopsy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
